      • intersectRay

        public double intersectRay​(Vector direction,
                           Location location)
        Calculates the first intersection betwen this AABB and the given ray. Assuming the ray is described as d * t + l, where l is a point in the ray and d is the direction of the ray, this method returns the smallest non-negative t for which the ray intersects the AABB. If no intersection is found, Double.MAX_VALUE is returned
        Parameters:
        direction - Direction of the ray casted
        location - A point on the ray
        Returns:
        Smallest multiple of the direction leading to an intersection or Double.MAX_VALUE if no intersection is found
